                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1066: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-09T12:00:00-02:00"
                            >February 9, 1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 9—11
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. The following memorandum of Brazil’s position on February 9 was handed to me
                    this morning by the Foreign Minister.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“We hold to our formula, inasmuch as it was adopted by all the American
                        Governments and by the League of Nations. If, however, in order to obtain
                        the consent of the two interested states it should be necessary for Brazil
                        to extend a little longer the period of her temporary occupation of the
                        territory, for instance to 60 days, Brazil will make the sacrifice of
                        accepting that honorable task.</p>
                    <p>In such a case it would be desirable to establish the manner in which that
                        period should be established: whether from the date of the convention, the
                        date of the arrival of the two commissions at Rio de Janeiro, or the date
                        the Brazilian delegate at Leticia should assume his duties.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Your 25 [<hi rend="italic">24?</hi>] February 8, 5 p.m. I expect to send today
                    the text of the latest Brazilian proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
